<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Mary Janes have ascended to cult status of late, and the look is sticking around for spring. But, of course, some versions are sweeter than others. Sandy Liang and Coach showcased classic and twee versionsâ€”the latter opting for iconic styling with socks. Meanwhile, Prada debuted a modern cowboy boot hybrid, while Versace gave us the heftier version to properly ground your punk and grunge looks.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><em>Bad Girls Club</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/gucci-gettyimages-1664580404.jpg?crop=1xw:1xh;center,top&amp;resize=480:*" alt="models on a runway wearing spring 2023 shoe trends" title="Spring 2023 Shoe Trends "/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>GETTY IMAGES</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>From S&amp;M to punk, a rebellious chord struck many a fall collection, and the vibe continues into spring. When getting your rebel fix, think about juxtaposition when styling. A strappy patent platform is divine in combination with an occasion mini, yes, but chain-laced boots and brogues are a stylish offset to dresses and skirts of all kinds.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
